01:00:27,120 --> 01:00:32,920
the metric and the tactic and the go-to-market 
all lined up, rather than sometimes in cases  

611
01:00:32,920 --> 01:00:36,320
you might hear someone say, "Well, let's make 
the product quality better." Well, we all make  

612
01:00:36,320 --> 01:00:41,760
the product quality better, but why? Why is this 
actually going to move what our customers want,  

613
01:00:41,760 --> 01:00:47,200
and the business board? And when you can line them 
all up, it can be quite beautiful, especially when  

614
01:00:47,200 --> 01:00:52,160
you can see it month-over-month for a long period 
of time. One other metric I think that I would  

615
01:00:52,160 --> 01:00:59,400
export to anybody, is if you are unsure what 
to measure, we have this, I don't know if we  

616
01:00:59,400 --> 01:01:04,520
